  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Statement.}\nFor any diffeomorphism $\\phi:M\\to M$ preserving the symmetry group of $M$,\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\phi(p)=p .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $\\phi:M\\to M$ be a diffeomorphism preserving the symmetry structure of the manifold. Since $p$ is defined as the unique point where the metric degeneracy occurs,\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\det(g)\\big|_p=0 .\n\\end{equation}\n\nIf $\\phi$ preserves the Trawinistic structure, then it must preserve the degeneracy locus:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\det(g)\\big|_{\\phi(p)}=0 .\n\\end{equation}\n\nBecause $p$ is unique, the only point satisfying this condition is $p$ itself. Therefore:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\phi(p)=p .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThe TZP is invariant under all structure-preserving transformations. It is therefore a fixed point of the system.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
